}$ at a given\nredshift. We find remarkably little scatter in the average trends and a strong\nevolution of $>$0.5 dex in the central density threshold correlated with\nquiescence from $z\\sim0.7-2.0$. Neither a compact size nor high-$n$ are\nsufficient to assess the likelihood of quiescence for the average galaxy;\nrather, the combination of these two parameters together with M$_{\\star}$\nresults in a unique quenching threshold in central density/velocity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Jul 2016 20:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 5 Oct 2016 01:12:22 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 21 Feb 2017 18:54:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-29"}
