t demonstrates that both problems are confined to group environments\nand must, therefore, owe to 'galaxy formation physics' rather than exotic\ncosmology.\n  Finally, we repeat our analysis for a $\\Lambda$ Warm Dark Matter cosmology,\nfinding that it fails at 68% confidence for a thermal relic mass of $m_{\\rm\nWDM} < 1.25$keV, and $m_{\\rm WDM} < 2$keV if we use the power law extrapolation\nof SDSS. We conclude by making a number of predictions for future surveys based\non these results.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Jul 2016 20:04:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Jan 2017 21:26:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2017 17:33:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-09"}
