rlinizing quantum protocols. This result claimed that, in any one-way\nquantum communication protocol where two parties are assisted by an\nall-powerful but untrusted third party, the third party can be removed with\nonly a modest increase in the communication cost. We give a corrected proof of\na key technical lemma required for Aaronson's result.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2016 06:23:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Oct 2016 08:14:36 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 21 Oct 2016 09:54:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-18"}
