ough,\ncompared to observations. For satellites, we find strong evidence that\nenvironment affects their quenched fraction at fixed central velocity\ndispersion, particularly at lower masses. At higher masses, satellites behave\nidentically to centrals in their quenching. Of the environmental parameters\nconsidered, local density affects the quenched fraction of satellites the most\nat fixed central velocity dispersion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2016 11:58:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-31"}
