ata from heterogeneous sites only slightly decreased our\nability to detect changes compared to a monosite study with the GLM, and had a\ngreater impact on prediction accuracy. Taken together, our results support the\nfeasibility of multisite studies in rs-fMRI provided the sample size is large\nenough.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2016 15:22:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Dec 2016 19:47:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 27 Jan 2017 17:57:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-10"}
